        <h2>
            About Swachhta Abhiyan System 
        </h2>
   
        <h4>
            <b style="font-size:large">“Swachhta Abhiyan System”</b> can be used as a national level to clean the streets, 
            roads and infrastructure of the country. Cleaning missing is one of the biggest challenge we are facing in country. <br>
         By using this online portal we can make aware people about swachata abhiyan so that they can participate and make country clean.
         <br><br>
         Main objective such as:<br>
    
        <ul>
            <li>Construction of individual, cluster and community toilets.</li>
            <li>To eliminate or reduce open defecation. Open defecation is one of the main causes of deaths of thousands of children each year.</li>
            <li>Not only latrine construction, the Swachata abhiyan system will also make an initiative of establishing an accountable mechanism of monitoring latrine use.</li>
            <li>Public awareness will also be provided about the drawbacks of open defecation and promotion of latrine use.</li>
            <li>Proper, dedicated ground staff will be recruited to bring about behavioral change and promotion of latrine use.</li>
            <li>For proper sanitation use, the mission will aim at changing people’s attitudes, mindsets and behaviors.</li>
            <li>Villages to be kept clean with Solid and Liquid Waste Management.</li>
            <li>Solid and liquid waste management through gram panchayats.</li>
            <li>To lay water pipelines in all villages, ensuring water supply to all households.</li>
            <li>To provide toilets, separately for Boys and Girls in all schools.</li>
            <li>To provide toilets to all Anganwadis</li>
           
        </ul>
        </h4>
        
        <br>
        <h2>
            Problem In Existing System
        </h2>
        <h4>
        <ul style="list-style: none;">
            
            <u>MANUAL OPERATION</u><br><br>
            <li> Today most of complain regarding toilet construction, solid or liquid wastage etc.  Are done manually that takes lot of time.</li><br>
                    <u>PROBLEM OF RELIABILITY</u><br><br>
                    <li>In manual Operation, it is difficult to maintain old information that may lead to inconsistency.</li><br>
                    <u>PROBLEM OF ACCURACY</u><br><br>
                    <li>Problem of accuracy occur when information obtained from corrupted officials who are not providing 
                        correct information work completed properly or not.</li><br>
                    <u>PROBLEM OF VALIDITY</u><br><br>
                    <li>In manual operation, there is very difficult to update all the information of the work done by swachata work.</li><br>
                    <u>DISTANCE PROBLEM</u><br><br>
                    <li>Sometime due to distance problem, people are not able to get proper information or not aware where to get knowledge about this.</li><br>
                    
        </ul>
        </h4>
        <br>
        <br>
        
        <h3>All above problems can be solved using Swachhta Abhiyan System.</h3>
        
        <br>
        <h2>
            Objective Of Our System
        </h2>
        <h4>
            The <b style="font-size:large">“Swachhta Abhiyan System”</b>objective is to provide a system which controls services of regarding 
            clean mission that is currently running , in this any people seeking help or want to complain regarding any undone work . 
            People can also get proper advice by sending their queries to concerned department and get answer from there.
 This will take less amount as compared to offline system. People need to visit anywhere they can see all the information from site and 
 also complain if anybody not following rules to make sure clean country.

            
        </h4>
        
